@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "cHEXx" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, the game requires a 68020(+)
Amiga with Workbench 2.0 or higher.

                             How to play?

  To play, just click on a coloured tile. If any unlinked tile of
the same type is located next, either horizontally or diagonally,
that tile will be linked to the clicked tile...

  The more links that are created in one move, the more points you
get. A single link give no points, however, two links or more give
a number of points, as shown in the following table:

    2 links =  1 point
    3 links =  4 points
    4 links =  9 points
    5 links = 16 points
    6 links = 25 points

  When all possible links have been made, the game board is
completed, and cHEXx will display a new game board...

  Have fun!

  You can quit the game by clicking on the game window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

@endnode

